---
/**
 * lsm-compaction-deep-dive · Figure 6 — Level 6 "L0, write stalls &
 * back-pressure": flushes feed L0 (overlapping, files piling up = compaction
 * debt), compaction drains toward L1/L2…, and the BACK-PRESSURE box
 * (slowdown_trigger → throttle, stop_trigger → STOP).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/storage-engines/lsm-compaction-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source page declared its arrowhead markers (#arw / #arwA / #arwG) ONCE in a
 * hidden top-of-body <svg defs>. Because each figure is now an isolated component,
 * the #arw (fill #6b675f) and #arwG (fill #2f5d3a) markers this figure references
 * via marker-end="url(#…)" are inlined here in a local <defs> so it resolves
 * standalone (verbatim from the source defs).
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 210"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Flushes feed L0 from the top; compaction drains it toward L1 and below. If the write rate exceeds the drain rate, L0 files pile up, compaction debt accrues, and the engine throttles then stops writes."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect x="30" y="14" width="120" height="34" rx="8" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text x="90" y="35" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                >writes → flush</text
            >
            <line x1="90" y1="48" x2="90" y2="64" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <!-- L0 with piling files -->
            <rect
                x="18"
                y="66"
                width="270"
                height="58"
                rx="8"
                fill="#f7ecea"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
            <text x="36" y="84" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417">L0</text>
            <text x="36" y="98" font-size="8" fill="#9a2417">overlapping</text>
            <g fill="#fff" stroke="#9a2417"
                ><rect x="96" y="74" width="26" height="40" rx="3"></rect><rect
                    x="126"
                    y="74"
                    width="26"
                    height="40"
                    rx="3"></rect><rect x="156" y="74" width="26" height="40" rx="3"></rect><rect
                    x="186"
                    y="74"
                    width="26"
                    height="40"
                    rx="3"></rect><rect x="216" y="74" width="26" height="40" rx="3"></rect><rect
                    x="246"
                    y="74"
                    width="26"
                    height="40"
                    rx="3"></rect></g
            >
            <text x="200" y="138" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
                >files pile up = "compaction debt" (pending bytes)</text
            >
            <!-- drain -->
            <line x1="288" y1="95" x2="330" y2="95" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
            <text x="309" y="87" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#2f5d3a">drain</text>
            <rect x="334" y="78" width="100" height="34" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text x="384" y="99" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#1f3a5a">L1, L2, …</text>
            <!-- back-pressure -->
            <rect
                x="448"
                y="40"
                width="100"
                height="120"
                rx="10"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
            <text
                x="498"
                y="60"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">BACK-PRESSURE</text
            >
            <text x="498" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110"
                >slowdown_trigger</text
            >
            <text x="498" y="97" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
                >→ throttle writes</text
            >
            <text
                x="498"
                y="122"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="8.5"
                fill="#9a2417"
                font-weight="700">stop_trigger</text
            >
            <text x="498" y="135" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
                >→ STOP writes</text
            >
            <text x="498" y="152" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >until L0 drains</text
            >
            <text x="200" y="180" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#111110"
                >write rate &gt; drain rate ⇒ L0 grows ⇒ engine deliberately throttles, then stops</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        A read must consult <em>every</em> L0 file (ranges overlap, so binary search can't pick one) —
        a fat L0 slows every read AND signals the tree is falling behind.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
